gomodel:SYNGO_111  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Using an specific antibody with knockout controls in STED microscopy, it is demonstrated that RIM-BP2 is localized in close proximity to Bassoon and Munc13-1. This shows that RIM-BP2 is localized to the active zone. This finding is in good agreement with STED microscopy performed in the fly NMJ (Liu et.al. 2011).\n\n3/2/2017 Pim\n- Fig 3: STED\n- S2G: EM. Experimental description: KO Mouse Generation.\n\nRIM-BP2 and RIM-BP1 targeting vector construction and KO mouse generation by standard homologous recombination were performed by genOway." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7620-2704" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1558-1958" ;
        dc:date           "2017-03-21" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_111" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

